<emphasis id="B91A9969F453FFAEFF656E635A1FF8FE" bold="true" box="[189,328,1863,1889]" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">Comments:</emphasis>
—The 28S rDNA sequence of the specimen on 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F453FFAEFCBF6E6C5889F8FE" box="[871,990,1863,1890]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Albizia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="12" pageNumber="139" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lebbeck">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F453FFAEFCBF6E6C5889F8FE" box="[871,990,1863,1890]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">A. lebbeck</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F37905EBF453FFAEFBFC6E635F30F8FE" box="[1060,1127,1863,1889]" name="Benin" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">Benin</collectingCountry>
indicates that it represents a species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F453FFAEFEDB6E4F5AB7F81A" authorityName="Magnus" authorityYear="1891" box="[259,480,1899,1925]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Raveneliaceae" genus="Sphaerophragmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="12" pageNumber="139" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F453FFAEFEDB6E4F5AB7F81A" box="[259,480,1899,1925]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">Sphaerophragmium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Three species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F453FFAEFD6E6E4F58C4F81A" authorityName="Magnus" authorityYear="1891" box="[694,915,1899,1925]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Raveneliaceae" genus="Sphaerophragmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="12" pageNumber="139" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F453FFAEFD6E6E4F58C4F81A" box="[694,915,1899,1925]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">Sphaerophragmium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are known on 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F453FFAEFB9B6E4F5F9BF819" box="[1091,1228,1899,1926]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Albizia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="12" pageNumber="139" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F453FFAEFB9B6E4F5FC5F81A" box="[1091,1170,1899,1925]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">Albizia</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
, namely 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F453FFAEFAEE6E485A1CF835" authority="(Cooke) Magnus" authorityName="Magnus" baseAuthorityName="Cooke" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Raveneliaceae" genus="Sphaerophragmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="12" pageNumber="139" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="acaciae">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F453FFAEFAEE6E485EFCF81A" box="[1334,1451,1900,1926]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">S. acaciae</emphasis>
(Cooke) Magnus
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F453FFAEFE826EB45864F835" authority="Lohsomb., Kakish. &amp; Y. Ono" authorityName="Lohsomb., Kakish. &amp; Y. Ono" box="[346,819,1935,1962]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Raveneliaceae" genus="Sphaerophragmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="12" pageNumber="139" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="albiziae">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F453FFAEFE826EB45A85F836" box="[346,466,1935,1962]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">S. albiziae</emphasis>
Lohsomb., Kakish. &amp; Y. Ono
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F453FFAEFCAC6EB45EDFF835" authority="Syd. (Lohsomboon et al. 1994)" box="[884,1416,1935,1962]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Raveneliaceae" genus="Sphaerophragmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="12" pageNumber="139" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="clemensiae">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F453FFAEFCAC6EB45F58F836" box="[884,1039,1935,1962]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">S. clemensiae</emphasis>
Syd. (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF388AF453FFAEFB866EAB5ED7F835" author="Lohsomboon, P. &amp; Kakishima, M. &amp; Ono, Y." box="[1118,1408,1935,1962]" pageId="12" pageNumber="139" pagination="907 - 919" refId="ref12267" refString="Lohsomboon, P., Kakishima, M. &amp; Ono, Y. (1994) A monograph of Sphaerophragmium (Uredinales). Mycological Research 98: 907 - 919. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / S 0953 - 7562 (09) 80262 - 1" type="journal article" year="1994">
Lohsomboon 
<emphasis id="B91A9969F453FFAEFB266EB45E64F836" box="[1278,1331,1935,1961]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">et al</emphasis>
. 1994
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F453FFAEFA4E6EB45B88F852" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Raveneliaceae" genus="Sphaerophragmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="12" pageNumber="139" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="acaciae">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F453FFAEFA4E6EB45B88F852" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">S. acaciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is reported from many countries with warm to hot climate, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F453FFAEFC606E905F7BF852" box="[952,1068,1971,1998]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Raveneliaceae" genus="Sphaerophragmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="12" pageNumber="139" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="albiziae">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F453FFAEFC606E905F7BF852" box="[952,1068,1971,1998]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">S. albiziae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F453FFAEFBB96E905FAFF852" box="[1121,1272,1971,1998]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Raveneliaceae" genus="Sphaerophragmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="12" pageNumber="139" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="clemensiae">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F453FFAEFBB96E905FAFF852" box="[1121,1272,1971,1998]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">S. clemensiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are only known from 
<collectingCountry id="F37905EBF453FFAEFF1D6EFC5A65F86E" box="[197,306,2007,2034]" name="China" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">East Asia</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F453FFAEFEE46EFC5AE6F86E" box="[316,433,2007,2034]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Raveneliaceae" genus="Sphaerophragmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="12" pageNumber="139" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="albiziae">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F453FFAEFEE46EFC5AE6F86E" box="[316,433,2007,2034]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">S. albiziae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forms amphigenous uredinia and urediniospores that are longer than those of the specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F37905EBF453FFAEFF116EDF5A58F78A" box="[201,271,2043,2069]" name="Benin" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">Benin</collectingCountry>
, i.e., 24–39 µm (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF388AF453FFAEFE016EDF59AFF789" author="Lohsomboon, P. &amp; Kakishima, M. &amp; Ono, Y." box="[473,760,2043,2070]" pageId="12" pageNumber="139" pagination="907 - 919" refId="ref12267" refString="Lohsomboon, P., Kakishima, M. &amp; Ono, Y. (1994) A monograph of Sphaerophragmium (Uredinales). Mycological Research 98: 907 - 919. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / S 0953 - 7562 (09) 80262 - 1" type="journal article" year="1994">
Lohsomboon 
<emphasis id="B91A9969F453FFAEFDA16ED859FAF78A" box="[633,685,2043,2069]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">et al</emphasis>
. 1994
</bibRefCitation>
) vs. 22–26 µm (specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F37905EBF453FFAEFBAC6EDF5FEBF789" box="[1140,1212,2043,2070]" name="Benin" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">Benin</collectingCountry>
). The urediniospores of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F452FFAFFF7069BB5A15FF27" box="[168,322,158,185]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Raveneliaceae" genus="Sphaerophragmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="13" pageNumber="140" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="clemensiae">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F452FFAFFF7069BB5A15FF27" box="[168,322,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="140">S. clemensiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are as long as those of the present specimen, but they are slenderer than those from 
<collectingCountry id="F37905EBF452FFAFFAC869BA5E04FF27" box="[1296,1363,158,184]" name="Benin" pageId="13" pageNumber="140">Benin</collectingCountry>
(16–18 µm) by being 12–17 µm wide (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF388AF452FFAFFE2C69E65844FF43" author="Lohsomboon, P. &amp; Kakishima, M. &amp; Ono, Y." box="[500,787,194,221]" pageId="13" pageNumber="140" pagination="907 - 919" refId="ref12267" refString="Lohsomboon, P., Kakishima, M. &amp; Ono, Y. (1994) A monograph of Sphaerophragmium (Uredinales). Mycological Research 98: 907 - 919. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / S 0953 - 7562 (09) 80262 - 1" type="journal article" year="1994">
Lohsomboon 
<emphasis id="B91A9969F452FFAFFD4B69E75990FF43" box="[659,711,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="140">et al</emphasis>
. 1994
</bibRefCitation>
). With a size of (18–)22–26(–27) × (15–)16–18(–20) µm, the urediniospores of the present specimen are within the size range of those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F452FFAFFBEF69C35FF9FE9F" box="[1079,1198,231,257]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Raveneliaceae" genus="Sphaerophragmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="13" pageNumber="140" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="acaciae">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F452FFAFFBEF69C35FF9FE9F" box="[1079,1198,231,257]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="140">S. acaciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(20–33 × 14–25 µm; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF388AF452FFAFFF50682E5ACDFEBB" author="Lohsomboon, P. &amp; Kakishima, M. &amp; Ono, Y." box="[136,410,266,293]" pageId="13" pageNumber="140" pagination="907 - 919" refId="ref12267" refString="Lohsomboon, P., Kakishima, M. &amp; Ono, Y. (1994) A monograph of Sphaerophragmium (Uredinales). Mycological Research 98: 907 - 919. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / S 0953 - 7562 (09) 80262 - 1" type="journal article" year="1994">
Lohsomboon 
<emphasis id="B91A9969F452FFAFFEFA682F5A05FEBB" box="[290,338,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="140">et al</emphasis>
. 1994
</bibRefCitation>
). Further similarities are the exclusively hypophyllous position of the uredinia and 4 to 5 germ pores on each urediniospore which are however difficult to see. Based on these similarities, the specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F37905EBF452FFAFFAB0680A5EFCFED7" box="[1384,1451,302,328]" name="Benin" pageId="13" pageNumber="140">Benin</collectingCountry>
is identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F452FFAFFEEA68775AF2FEF3" box="[306,421,339,365]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Raveneliaceae" genus="Sphaerophragmium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="13" pageNumber="140" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="acaciae">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F452FFAFFEEA68775AF2FEF3" box="[306,421,339,365]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="140">S. acaciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and represents the first report for 
<collectingCountry id="F37905EBF452FFAFFCFB6876583DFEF3" box="[803,874,338,364]" name="Benin" pageId="13" pageNumber="140">Benin</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
